Fig. 15. Feature representation clusters for clean CIFAR10 models. This Ô¨Ågure shows class 0 and 7. The left column shows the feature representations of the translated and the training images, whereas the right column shows the result of the Mean shift clustering on the corresponding points where different colours represent different classes.
Fig. 16. Feature representation clusters for clean CIFAR10 models from Madry-Lab. This Ô¨Ågure shows class 0. The left column shows the feature representations of the translated and the training images, whereas the right column shows the result of the Mean shift clustering on the corresponding points where different colours represent different classes. It is important to note that the translated images and training set images form separate clusters.

